-----------------------------
* Elastic cloud compute (EC2)
-----------------------------

 Basically you get a machine and you get to choose what you want like os, ram, cpu , space etc.
 we call it instance.
 we can enable ssh and http / https traffic on it.
 also, we can define multiple layer of rules to make it behave certain way or to make it more secure.
 

-----------------
* Security Groups
-----------------

 Network firewall rules that control inbound and outbound traffic for instances


--------------
* Common Ports
--------------

------------------------------------------------------------------
 Http        |  80     |  Unencrypted web traffic
------------------------------------------------------------------
 Https       |  443    |  Encrypted web traffic ( SSL/TSL )
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 SSH         |  22     |  Secure remote access to servers
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 FTP         |  21     |  File Transfer Protocol (unsecured)
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 SFTP        |  22     |  Secure File transfer protocol
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 SMTP        |  25     |  Simple Mail Transfer Protocol ( email )
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 RDP         |  3389   |  Remote desktop control
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 MYsQL       |  3306   |  MYSQL Database connection
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 PostGreSQL  |  5432   |  PostGRESQL Database connection
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 DNS		 |  53     |  Domain Name System
 -----------------------------------------------------------------
 
 
 
 
